{meta: title Enclosed One Broken Heart}
{meta: artist Eddy Arnold}
{meta: writer Sadie Nordin Sallis and Eddy Arnold}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G7]Enclosed you'll find one broken [C]heart
In [G7]need of much [C]repair
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
You'll find it wrapped in tears I've shed
[G7]Because I won't [C]be [G7]there
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
This heart won't laugh [C]and it won't sing
In [G7]fact the beating [C]stopped
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
You say there was no guarantee
And [G7]most things break when [C]dropped
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Then one day dear you answer came
And [G7]there all wrapped with [C]care
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Was my poor heart in pieces still
And [G7]marked beyond [C]repair
{end_of_verse}
